    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hard, fine-grained wood of the species Acer saccharum, native to the United States and Canada. It is light reddish-brown in color and tends to have bird's eye patterns. It is used for furniture, cabinetry, flooring (dance floors, bowling alleys), musical instruments, and veneer.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
